My go-to salad place. Very reasonable prices, especially for the FiDi. Great flavors and selection. You can customize your salad if you want to, and if you don't, there are great pre-designed salads.  Can get somewhat crowded around 12pm, but that's the only drawback.

This location is a great place to buy. Chains and eateries are a balance of the experience, the service, consistency and the food. This is a mix few people seem to get. At this location that's not the case. They have great food at a somewhat affordable price. But most importantly they have a staff team that is very friendly amenable and accommodating. I have gotten to the point where I am feeling a familiarity and building a rapport with them. They get it right here. Rather than getting offended or frustrated with complications in filling orders or high stress lunch rushes, they are patient and focus on closing the sale the right way. With the customer service as significant as they make it, they are able to keep the experience of patronizing the location satisfying even if something undesirable occurs every now and then. I've had three messed up on-line orders in a row and each time they've been great about pointing out the issues with the orders and working with me to complete the order in the store. I can't say enough good about them.
